It is an Afghan tradition to visit the graves of ancestors during Eid to have a picnic and honour the dead.

The victims of the Nangarhar graveyard bomb were mostly from a single family, according to a spokesman for the provincial governor.

In addition to the 14 dead, a child and three women were injured.

Nangarhar and its capital, Jalalabad, have been racked by a series of bombings and suicide attacks over the last week.

