Elsewhere, three Afghan bodyguards for the Helmand province police chief, Mohammad Hakim Angaar, were killed on Wednesday in a suicide bombing.

In June, a suicide bomber rammed an explosives-laden car into the former Helmand police chief's convoy, wounding three.

Western forces have been desperately trying to improve the security situation before they pull out of Afghanistan next year.

However, continued attacks by the Taliban and incidents of Afghan soldiers turning against their Nato handlers have put that deadline in question.

